column1: SDG 4.3 By 2030, ensure equal access for all women and men to affordable and quality technical,vocational and tertiary education, including university
Definition: Number of years of schooling that a child of school entrance age can expect to receive if prevailing patterns of age-specific enrolment rates persist throughout the child's life.
Source: UNESCO Institute for Statistics (2020), ICF Macro Demographic and Health Surveys, UNICEF Multiple Indicator Cluster Surveys and OECD (2019b).

column2: Organization for Economic Co-operation and Development

column1: a: Data refer to 2019 or the most recent year available.
b: Based on data from the national statistical office.
c: Updated by HDRO based on data from ICF Macro Demographic and Health Surveys for 2006-2019.
d: Updated by HDRO based on data from UNESCO Institute for Statistics (2020).
e: In calculating the HDI value, expected years of schooling is capped at 18 years.
g: Updated by HDRO based on data from CEDLAS and World Bank (2020).
h: Updated by HDRO based on data from United Nations Children’s Fund (UNICEF) Multiple Indicator Cluster Surveys for 2006–2019.
i: Based on data from OECD (2019b).
